10/10 VR game, it's fun for everyone (if they have enough space to play).
I would recommend this game if you're a vr veteran meaning you'll probably not go vomitting after playing. There are some pros and cons to this game i will list them below:

Cons - Having a small space and possibly hitting something in real life while playing, getting mad easily, possibly not get used to the cosmetics that cover a little of your face, getting tagged all the time, bad pc.

Pros - Having a big playspace/space, not hitting something in real life, getting used to the game really quick, learning special tricks (Wall climbing, wall run...), getting already used to the cosmetics, avoid getting tagged for more than 10 minutes, having a powerful pc to play with little to no lag, getting out of the map.

What can i say? Theres a bunch of pros and cons. For you new gorillas at the game you should try to be careful of your area and try your best to recenter your self by moving to the middle of your play area if you move out of it really fast, learn how to wall run and wall climb and possibly get out of the map!

Love the idea, but, it's extremely glitchy. With almost all climbing activities, your hands WILL get stuck inside whatever it is your climbing on, resulting in an inability to move, and when it finally releases, being jolted uncontrollably.

My other big complaint is it's virtually impossible to play in a public lobby with friends because their matchmaking always places you in a full lobby in my experience.

Also, this isn't suitable for children in public lobbies. The inappropriate conversations and toxicity of some people's voice chat is rather bad. I'd strongly encourage some kind of AI censor, or AI moderation, or have default public lobbies have no voice chat.

Other than that, great game.

To get the obvious out of the way, it is very easy to exploit. Whenever im in a public lobby, there's at least someone trying to glitch out the map. People also like to use mods (Long arms, Tag all, platforms etc) which heavily makes the game less fun. The other thing which makes this game worse is the player base. Children on the game is fine, but sometimes, they are really toxic or racist (I do know there's a report button I just want to clarify). But the things i like was that there's no complex button controls which makes it easier for beginners and makes it fast to get used to the game, there's weekly updates/patches (Maps and cosmetics) and the game is just fun in general. The content coming from the player base is wierd but that makes it unique. Overall, this is a really good game coming from unity.
